[2026-07-01T04:22:06Z] PRE-TOOL-USE: INPUT: {"session_id":"8bfddf72-bc04-4de9-ad9b-f9229f251ba4","transcript_path":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-jackw-Desktop-PoolHop\\8bfddf72-bc04-4de9-ad9b-f9229f251ba4.jsonl","cwd":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\Desktop\\PoolHop","prompt_id":"7a9bc8a6-8aac-49e3-b4b6-443146978e0d","permission_mode":"bypassPermissions","effort":{"level":"max"},"hook_event_name":"PreToolUse","tool_name":"Edit","tool_input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\Desktop\\PoolHop\\Docs\\LESSONS.md","old_string":"## 2026-06-30 — Session: System 1 (movement)","new_string":"## 2026-06-30 — Session: System 1 (movement)\n\n### PIE froze at \"Recreating Persistent SBTs\" — template Lumen hardware ray tracing deadlocked\n**Signature:** PIE starts fast and clean (`Play in editor total start time 0.149s`), then the whole editor freezes. The UE log stops dead at `LogRenderer: Recreating Persistent SBTs due to initializer changes ... NumGeometrySegments 0 → 512`. **This is NOT a resource problem** — verified: RAM had 11.8 GB free, all disks had hundreds of GB free, **0 ShaderCompileWorker** processes, main editor CPU moved only ~0.7 CPU-s over 4 s (idle, not compiling), GPU at 11% (not rendering-heavy), and `Get-Process ... Responding = True`. Idle CPU + idle GPU + frozen log = a **stall/deadlock**, not slow work. \"SBT\" = ray-tracing Shader Binding Table → the freeze is in **hardware ray tracing** init.\n**Cause:** the ThirdPerson template ships `r.RayTracing=True` (Config/DefaultEngine.ini, `[/Script/Engine.RendererSettings]`) with Lumen (`r.DynamicGlobalIlluminationMethod=1`), DX12/SM6. Building the RT scene hung on first PIE.\n**Fix:** set `r.RayTracing=False` in DefaultEngine.ini (a **startup** cvar — the editor must be restarted to apply). Lumen falls back to software ray tracing; a grey-box movement test needs no HWRT. Also repointed `EditorStartupMap`/`GameDefaultMap` to `L_Sandbox_Movement`. **Diagnosing a frozen editor:** read `Saved/Logs/*.log` mtime + tail (file read, not MCP), sample process CPU delta over a few seconds, and check GPU utilization — don't fire MCP calls that queue behind the blocked game thread. Recovery from the hang required force-closing the editor (all work was saved + committed, so no loss).\n","replace_all":false},"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TiRBYJchrUkp8xxChsuCWP"}
