t yourself (one time)\nHit **Play**, then **click once inside the game window** so it has keyboard focus, and press **W**. You'll now watch Manny move. That single hardware keypress is the only thing I physically can't send into the editor from here — but it's proven to work.\n\n## Two honest caveats (both cosmetic, both fixable)\n1. **Manny is grey** — his material files (`MI_Manny_*`) are still 0-byte from the original asset corruption, so he falls back to the default grey material.\n2. **He slides in a static pose** — the project has no animation Blueprint, so there's no walk cycle yet.\n\nNeither affects movement or the build. Want me to knock those out next (get him properly colored + animated), or leave cosmetics and push on to the next system (Loudness → Scoring per the roadmap)?","background_tasks":[],"session_crons":[]}
