[2026-07-01T15:24:45Z] STOP-HOOK: INPUT: {"session_id":"8bfddf72-bc04-4de9-ad9b-f9229f251ba4","transcript_path":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-jackw-Desktop-PoolHop\\8bfddf72-bc04-4de9-ad9b-f9229f251ba4.jsonl","cwd":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\Desktop\\PoolHop","prompt_id":"eb1483cc-ccff-413a-8884-645f9bb9ba05","permission_mode":"bypassPermissions","effort":{"level":"xhigh"},"hook_event_name":"Stop","stop_hook_active":false,"last_assistant_message":"I finally have the actual root cause — and it's not anything I was chasing before. **The game was never frozen. It's rendering at ~1-2 FPS.** The engine's own frame counter proves it: it rendered only ~329 frames in 6.5 minutes. At 1 FPS, a game is indistinguishable from frozen, and it's also why my screenshots/auto-walk \"passed\" (a single frame and slow movement look fine at 1 FPS).\n\n**Why:** your RTX 5080 is brand-new Blackwell hardware, and UE 5.8 defaults to its heaviest renderer — Lumen GI, MegaLights, Virtual Shadow Maps, volumetric clouds. That combo has documented frametime problems on RTX 50-series and tanks the full game-render path to a crawl, even though the lighter editor viewport renders fine.\n\n**What I did:** rewrote the render config to a lightweight grey-box profile (Lumen/MegaLights/VSM/volumetric clouds off, PSO disk-cache on) and relaunched the game. I'm now **measuring the actual framerate from the engine logs myself** — at 60 FPS the frame counter rockets into the thousands in under a minute; at the old 1-2 FPS it stays in the dozens. I'll report the measured number and only hand it to you once it's confirmed playable. Give me ~3 minutes for the measurement to complete.","background_tasks":[{"id":"bdmlwfnez","type":"shell","status":"running","description":"Measure standalone game FPS from frame counter","command":"$log = \"C:\\Users\\jackw\\Desktop\\PoolHop\\Saved\\Logs\\PoolHop.log\"\nfunction Get-Frame { param($l) $m = Get-Content $l -Tail 4 -EA SilentlyContinue | Select-String -Patte