ll see the result instantly — in the game, press **`~`** and type **`stat fps`**.\n\n**2. Let me flip the project to DX11.** Reports say the RTX 5080 is far more stable on DX11 in UE5 right now. I can set that in one config line (it needs a one-time shader recompile, ~2 min). **Want me to do this now?**\n\n**3. Driver:** 610.62 is in the flagged range — updating to the latest NVIDIA **Studio** driver (or rolling back per the reports) is the durable fix once Epic/NVIDIA reconcile Blackwell.\n\nI've committed the lightweight render profile regardless (`788a0ba`) — it's the right setup for the grey-box phase. But the needle-mover is the GPU driver/power setting above, because the bottleneck is the card's clocks, not the scene.\n\nTell me: **want me to apply the DX11 switch while you do the power-mode toggle?** That's two shots at it in parallel.\n\nSources: [Epic — RTX 50-series driver known issues](https://dev.epicgames.com/community/learning/knowledge-base/44lX/unreal-engine-tech-note-known-issues-with-nvidia-576-xx-drivers-on-rtx-50-series-gpus) · [Epic forums — Known issues with RTX 5000-series GPUs](https://forums.unrealengine.com/t/known-issues-with-rtx-5000-series-gpus/2619821) · [NVIDIA forums — RTX 50 G-Sync/underclock stutter](https://www.nvidia.com/en-us/geforce/forums/game-ready-drivers/13/557645/rtx-5090-g-sync-vrr-micro-stutter/) · [NeoGAF — 610.x driver perf regression, rollback fix](https://www.neogaf.com/threads/anyone-else-having-performance-stutter-issues-on-the-newest-nvidia-610-47-drivers-rolling-back-to-596-49-fixed-it.1697474/)","background_tasks":[],"session_crons":[]}
