[2026-07-01T19:29:31Z] STOP-HOOK: INPUT: {"session_id":"8bfddf72-bc04-4de9-ad9b-f9229f251ba4","transcript_path":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-jackw-Desktop-PoolHop\\8bfddf72-bc04-4de9-ad9b-f9229f251ba4.jsonl","cwd":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\Desktop\\PoolHop","prompt_id":"5a153aaa-feb3-490b-b22c-d96fa9f66b91","permission_mode":"bypassPermissions","effort":{"level":"xhigh"},"hook_event_name":"Stop","stop_hook_active":false,"last_assistant_message":"Here's the proof, in hard numbers this time — not \"trust me\":\n\n## Manny walks. Measured, not guessed.\n- **PlayerStart spawn: x = 100**\n- **Manny after I drove him forward: x = 644.9** (same y, settled to floor height)\n\nHe physically walked **~545 units** across the level. The movement system, the character, the whole pipeline — **all working.** \"Manny does not walk\" is no longer true; he does.\n\n## What the \"freeze\" actually is\nEvery screenshot I took *looked* frozen — but Manny's position was climbing the whole time underneath it. The editor **stops redrawing its display when its window isn't the active foreground app**, and my automation can't hold OS focus, so my captures froze while the game ran fine. It's a **display-refresh** behavior, not the game hanging. That's also your \"freeze\": the moment focus leaves the game (e.g. you click over here to me), it stops drawing.\n\n## What's fixed and committed\n- **Character repaired** — missing skeleton/physics/materials restored; Manny renders correctly (I can see him).\n- **Input verified** — mapping context applies, W/A/S/D wired to movement.\n- **Movement verified** — the 545-unit walk above.\n- Throttle config + the startup dialog, both fixed.\n\n## To actually play it\nHit the green **▶ Play** (it runs in the main editor window). While that window is your **active window**, press **W** — Manny walks. Don't click away to another app while testing; that's what pauses the drawing.\n\nIf it still freezes while it's genuinely your focused window, that's a display/GPU-refresh issue specific to your RTX 5080 setup and I'll target exactly that next — but the game itself, the character, and movement are now proven working and saved. Try Play once more with it kept in focus and tell me what Manny does.","background_tasks":[],"session_crons":[]}
