[2026-07-01T19:31:44Z] PRE-TOOL-USE: INPUT: {"session_id":"8bfddf72-bc04-4de9-ad9b-f9229f251ba4","transcript_path":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-jackw-Desktop-PoolHop\\8bfddf72-bc04-4de9-ad9b-f9229f251ba4.jsonl","cwd":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\Desktop\\PoolHop","prompt_id":"5fba4fac-4ad5-4aa8-8d8d-1f8cab37dbf2","permission_mode":"bypassPermissions","effort":{"level":"xhigh"},"hook_event_name":"PreToolUse","tool_name":"Edit","tool_input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\Desktop\\PoolHop\\CLAUDE.md","old_string":"Re-test whether the repaired skeleton alone resolves the \"can't move\"/perf symptom before chasing the RTX50 render angle again.**","new_string":"Re-test whether the repaired skeleton alone resolves the \"can't move\"/perf symptom before chasing the RTX50 render angle again.**\n\n**RESOLVED (2026-07-01 evening — MCP reconnected, diagnosed live).** With editor control back: (1) Manny now **renders correctly** (repaired skeleton/materials). (2) **Movement PROVEN** — drove an auto-walk probe and read the pawn's `CollisionCylinder.RelativeLocation`: it walked from spawn `x=100` to `x=645` (~545 units). Input wiring + `IMC_Default` application were already verified. (3) **The \"freeze\" = Unreal's not-foreground throttle, not a perf bug** — the GPU idles at 3% util / 1852 MHz when the editor window isn't the OS-foreground app, and boosts to full 2800 MHz when it is (grey box ≈ 10% util). My screenshots only *looked* frozen because automation can't hold OS focus (Windows blocks `SetForegroundWindow` from background procs); the pawn moved underneath. Set `t.IdleWhenNotForeground=0` + `bThrottleCPUWhenNotForeground=False`. **For the user:** play with the game window as the active/focused window and press W → Manny walks. All probes removed; committed. **Still open:** if *focused* in-viewport play still stutters, verify the editor throttle is actually honored for PIE (may need a different mechanism); and assign `ABP_Unarmed` so Manny animates instead of sliding. **Measurement rule (see LESSONS):** the log `[N]` frame counter is unreliable — measure movement via pawn `RelativeLocation`, perf via `nvidia-smi`.","replace_all":false},"tool_use_id":"toolu_015AKRiGn7LjMCykTqC9AHj3"}
