[2026-07-01T19:48:27Z] PRE-TOOL-USE: INPUT: {"session_id":"8bfddf72-bc04-4de9-ad9b-f9229f251ba4","transcript_path":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-jackw-Desktop-PoolHop\\8bfddf72-bc04-4de9-ad9b-f9229f251ba4.jsonl","cwd":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\Desktop\\PoolHop","prompt_id":"5b8ecc92-d102-494c-9cae-310ed9fdb556","permission_mode":"bypassPermissions","effort":{"level":"xhigh"},"hook_event_name":"PreToolUse","tool_name":"Edit","tool_input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\Desktop\\PoolHop\\Docs\\LESSONS.md","old_string":"Stripping Lumen/MegaLights/VSM/clouds did nothing because the GPU was never the bottleneck. Mitigations set: `t.IdleWhenNotForeground=0` ([SystemSettings]) + `bThrottleCPUWhenNotForeground=False` (EditorPerformanceSettings). The reliable user workaround: keep the game window as the active/focused window.","new_string":"Stripping Lumen/MegaLights/VSM/clouds did nothing because the GPU was never the bottleneck. **CONFIRMED ROOT CAUSE + FIX:** `bThrottleCPUWhenNotForeground` was **`True` at runtime** — my `.ini` edits to `[/Script/UnrealEd.EditorPerformanceSettings]` never applied (`UEditorPerformanceSettings` is `config=EditorPerProjectUserSettings`, and the Saved config written on a prior editor-close overrode my Default edit). Read the live value to confirm: `ObjectTools.get_properties(\"/Script/UnrealEd.Default__EditorPerformanceSettings\", [\"bThrottleCPUWhenNotForeground\"])` → `true`. Fix it on the CDO directly: `set_properties(...Default__EditorPerformanceSettings, '{\"bThrottleCPUWhenNotForeground\": false}')` — takes effect immediately. **Verified end-to-end** with a slow (WalkSpeed=80) auto-walk toward the far −X wall: the pawn moved x=−1025 → −1464 during a **5 s *unfocused* wait** (before the fix it stayed frozen). The CDO value persists to the Saved config when the editor closes; `Config/DefaultEditorPerProjectUserSettings.ini` carries it for fresh clones. (`t.IdleWhenNotForeground=0` was a red herring — that's standalone-game, not PIE-in-editor.) **Diagnosis trap that cost time:** the pawn kept reaching a *perimeter wall* during warmup before the first position read, so \"stationary\" looked like \"frozen\" — to test tick-vs-blocked, slow the walk and aim at the *farthest* wall so you sample it mid-travel.","replace_all":false},"tool_use_id":"toolu_019im9qqqMocp87XBABfkPr9"}
