[2026-07-01T19:48:54Z] PRE-TOOL-USE: INPUT: {"session_id":"8bfddf72-bc04-4de9-ad9b-f9229f251ba4","transcript_path":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-jackw-Desktop-PoolHop\\8bfddf72-bc04-4de9-ad9b-f9229f251ba4.jsonl","cwd":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\Desktop\\PoolHop","prompt_id":"5b8ecc92-d102-494c-9cae-310ed9fdb556","permission_mode":"bypassPermissions","effort":{"level":"xhigh"},"hook_event_name":"PreToolUse","tool_name":"Edit","tool_input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\Desktop\\PoolHop\\CLAUDE.md","old_string":"Set `t.IdleWhenNotForeground=0` + `bThrottleCPUWhenNotForeground=False`. **For the user:** play with the game window as the active/focused window and press W → Manny walks. All probes removed; committed. **Still open:** if *focused* in-viewport play still stutters, verify the editor throttle is actually honored for PIE (may need a different mechanism); and assign `ABP_Unarmed` so Manny animates instead of sliding.","new_string":"**CONFIRMED FIX:** the freeze was `bThrottleCPUWhenNotForeground` = **True at runtime** (my `.ini` edits never applied). Set it False directly on the CDO — `ObjectTools.set_properties(\"/Script/UnrealEd.Default__EditorPerformanceSettings\", '{\"bThrottleCPUWhenNotForeground\": false}')` — and **verified the pawn moves during a 5 s *unfocused* wait** (x −1025→−1464). The game now ticks/renders regardless of focus; the freeze is gone. All probes removed, WalkSpeed restored to 600, committed. Persists via the editor's config-save-on-close + the project `Config/DefaultEditorPerProjectUserSettings.ini`. **Remaining polish (not blockers):** assign `ABP_Unarmed` to `CharacterMesh0.AnimClass` so Manny animates instead of sliding in A-pose.","replace_all":false},"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MNXnsqDaRpsDGFx3Go2tEQ"}
