[2026-07-01T19:49:39Z] STOP-HOOK: INPUT: {"session_id":"8bfddf72-bc04-4de9-ad9b-f9229f251ba4","transcript_path":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-jackw-Desktop-PoolHop\\8bfddf72-bc04-4de9-ad9b-f9229f251ba4.jsonl","cwd":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\Desktop\\PoolHop","prompt_id":"5b8ecc92-d102-494c-9cae-310ed9fdb556","permission_mode":"bypassPermissions","effort":{"level":"xhigh"},"hook_event_name":"Stop","stop_hook_active":false,"last_assistant_message":"Fixed — and I verified it myself, no test on you.\n\n## The actual bug, found and killed\nThe freeze was Unreal's **\"Use Less CPU in Background\" throttle** (`bThrottleCPUWhenNotForeground`). At runtime it was reading **`True`** — my earlier config edits never actually took effect, so the game **stopped ticking entirely whenever its window wasn't the focused one.** Every time focus left the game (mouse released, you clicked over here), it froze dead. I set the flag to **`False` on the live settings object**, which takes effect immediately.\n\n## Proof I checked it myself (not you)\nI drove the character with a probe and read its **actual world position** the whole time (screenshots lie under the throttle; position doesn't):\n- Movement was **always working** — the pawn walked 500–1560 units in every direction I pointed it, hitting the level's perimeter walls. \"Manny doesn't walk\" was never true; he does.\n- **The fix, verified:** with the throttle off, I slowed the walk and pointed it at the far wall, then read the position across a **5-second window while the game was unfocused** — it moved **x = −1025 → −1464**. Before the fix, it stayed frozen when unfocused. So the game now runs whether or not it's the active window.\n\n## State now (all committed, `76b3a2a`)\n- Character repaired and rendering; movement proven; **freeze eliminated**; probe removed; WalkSpeed restored to 600. LESSONS + CLAUDE updated with the real root cause.\n\n**Hit Play and press W — Manny walks, and it won't freeze when you click away.** If the throttle ever creeps back after an editor restart, it's one toggle: *Editor Preferences → General → Performance → \"Use Less CPU when in Background\" = off.* You were right to make me do it myself — that's how the real cause finally surfaced.","background_tasks":[],"session_crons":[]}
