[2026-07-01T20:24:43Z] PRE-TOOL-USE: INPUT: {"session_id":"8bfddf72-bc04-4de9-ad9b-f9229f251ba4","transcript_path":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-jackw-Desktop-PoolHop\\8bfddf72-bc04-4de9-ad9b-f9229f251ba4.jsonl","cwd":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\Desktop\\PoolHop","prompt_id":"c9e8a2a8-e349-42e8-afa4-52ae61238fd1","permission_mode":"bypassPermissions","effort":{"level":"xhigh"},"hook_event_name":"PreToolUse","tool_name":"Edit","tool_input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\Desktop\\PoolHop\\CLAUDE.md","old_string":"**RESOLVED (2026-07-01 evening — MCP reconnected, diagnosed live).** With editor control back: (1) Manny now **renders correctly** (repaired skeleton/materials). (2) **Movement PROVEN** — drove an auto-walk probe and read the pawn's `CollisionCylinder.RelativeLocation`: it walked from spawn `x=100` to `x=645` (~545 units). Input wiring + `IMC_Default` application were already verified. (3) **The \"freeze\" = Unreal's not-foreground throttle, not a perf bug** — the GPU idles at 3% util / 1852 MHz when the editor window isn't the OS-foreground app, and boosts to full 2800 MHz when it is (grey box ≈ 10% util). My screenshots only *looked* frozen because automation can't hold OS focus (Windows blocks `SetForegroundWindow` from background procs); the pawn moved underneath. **CONFIRMED FIX:** the freeze was `bThrottleCPUWhenNotForeground` = **True at runtime** (my `.ini` edits never applied). Set it False directly on the CDO — `ObjectTools.set_properties(\"/Script/UnrealEd.Default__EditorPerformanceSettings\", '{\"bThrottleCPUWhenNotForeground\": false}')` — and **verified the pawn moves during a 5 s *unfocused* wait** (x −1025→−1464). The game now ticks/renders regardless of focus; the freeze is gone. All probes removed, WalkSpeed restored to 600, committed. Persists via the editor's config-save-on-close + the project `Config/DefaultEditorPerProjectUserSettings.ini`. **Remaining polish (not blockers):** assign `ABP_Unarmed` to `CharacterMesh0.AnimClass` so Manny animates instead of sliding in A-pose. **Measurement rule (see LESSONS):** the log `[N]` frame counter is unreliable — measure movement via pawn `RelativeLocation`, perf via `nvidia-smi`.","new_string":"**✅ RESOLVED (2026-07-01 late PM — MCP reconnected, diagnosed live). The game was NEVER frozen — it runs at ~120 fps.** The entire perf/throttle narrative above was wrong. Measured live: two tool calls 0.379 s apart advanced the frame counter `844→889` = **119 fps** (confirm with tight, <1 s samples to avoid the counter's 1000-wrap ambiguity). **The \"freeze\" was a motionless A-pose statue:** `BP_PlayerCharacter.CharacterMesh0.AnimClass` was `None`, so Manny stood perfectly still — a 120 fps game showing a rigid, non-idling mannequin looks *identical* to a frozen frame. **FIX (commit `d4073d2`):** assigned `ABP_Unarmed` to `CharacterMesh0.AnimClass`; verified live — the pose changed A-pose→relaxed idle and the character pixels move frame-to-frame (~4800 px/frame), i.e. he's now visibly breathing/animating and will walk when moving. **Everything else verified working:** GameMode spawns+possesses `BP_PlayerCharacter_C` (found the live PIE pawn), controller BeginPlay applies `IMC_Default`→`SetInputMode_GameOnly` (runtime mouse-capture proves the IMC is live), `IA_Move` `Triggered`/`ActionValue` wired to the Move function (`get_node_infos`). `bThrottleCPUWhenNotForeground` is currently `False` (fine). **The one link MCP cannot self-test:** a *hardware* WASD press (Enhanced Input ignores synthetic keys; computer-use can't target the UE window — `request_access` returns `notInstalled`). If real WASD still doesn't move him despite the game being visibly alive, the only remaining suspect is **PIE keyboard focus in \"Play in Selected Viewport\"** — click once in the game view, or Play ▾ → \"New Editor Window.\" **Measurement rule (LESSONS):** confirm fps via <1 s frame-counter delta OR frame-to-frame pixel diff *before* any perf theory.","replace_all":false},"tool_use_id":"toolu_01N46DuoLC2T6QLEEYeD6a6D"}
