[2026-07-01T20:25:30Z] PRE-TOOL-USE: INPUT: {"session_id":"8bfddf72-bc04-4de9-ad9b-f9229f251ba4","transcript_path":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-jackw-Desktop-PoolHop\\8bfddf72-bc04-4de9-ad9b-f9229f251ba4.jsonl","cwd":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\Desktop\\PoolHop","prompt_id":"c9e8a2a8-e349-42e8-afa4-52ae61238fd1","permission_mode":"bypassPermissions","effort":{"level":"xhigh"},"hook_event_name":"PreToolUse","tool_name":"Write","tool_input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-jackw-Desktop-PoolHop\\memory\\freeze-was-static-anim-not-perf.md","content":"---\nname: freeze-was-static-anim-not-perf\ndescription: \"PoolHop's multi-session 'game freezes / can't move on Play' was a perception bug — 120fps + a motionless A-pose character, not a perf/throttle problem.\"\nmetadata:\n  type: project\n  originSessionId: 8bfddf72-bc04-4de9-ad9b-f9229f251ba4\n---\n\nThe user reported \"hit Play, it freezes, WASD does nothing\" many times across sessions. Two+ sessions were burned on wrong perf theories (RTX 5080/UE5.8 render bottleneck, shader stalls, `bThrottleCPUWhenNotForeground` throttle). **All wrong.** Measured live via MCP: the game runs at **~120 fps** (frame counter advanced 844→889 in 0.379 s). The real cause: `BP_PlayerCharacter.CharacterMesh0.AnimClass` was `None`, so Manny stood in a rigid **A-pose with zero idle animation** — a 120 fps game showing a motionless mannequin is visually identical to a frozen frame. Fixed by assigning `ABP_Unarmed` (commit `d4073d2`); verified he now idles/animates (pose changed + ~4800 px/frame of motion between captures).\n\n**Why this matters:** it cost enormous time and user trust (I declared \"fixed\" twice on wrong causes). The trap is treating a motionless *character* as evidence of a stalled *engine*.\n\n**How to apply:** when the user says \"frozen,\" FIRST prove whether the engine is ticking — two MCP tool calls <1 s apart and read the log `[N]` frame-counter delta (>~40 frames/sec = not frozen), or diff two `CaptureEditorImage` frames. Only after fps is confirmed low should perf theories start. Also: a character in ref/A-pose almost always means `AnimClass=None` on the mesh component — check that before anything exotic. The one link MCP genuinely can't test is a hardware keypress (Enhanced Input ignores synthetic keys; computer-use can't target the UE window). See [[update-lessons-live]] and `Docs/LESSONS.md` (2026-07-01 LATE PM entry).\n"},"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AvBWgXtAWeNToGZteZnvhX"}
