[2026-07-01T20:59:46Z] STOP-HOOK: INPUT: {"session_id":"8bfddf72-bc04-4de9-ad9b-f9229f251ba4","transcript_path":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-jackw-Desktop-PoolHop\\8bfddf72-bc04-4de9-ad9b-f9229f251ba4.jsonl","cwd":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\Desktop\\PoolHop","prompt_id":"195a987b-6897-409d-8050-b3d454160ec5","permission_mode":"bypassPermissions","effort":{"level":"xhigh"},"hook_event_name":"Stop","stop_hook_active":false,"last_assistant_message":"Deep research is in (25 agents, web-researched). It converges hard on one conclusion: **your keystrokes are being swallowed before Unreal ever sees them** — this symptom shape (keyboard-only, both play modes, types fine on the desktop, mouse seemingly alive, 100%-correct game wiring) is the textbook signature of an OS/keyboard-software layer eating the keys, *not* a bug in the game. The game is proven innocent.\n\nIt also flagged something important: the \"mouse works\" part is **unconfirmed** — your cursor vanishing on Play only proves Unreal *grabbed* the cursor, not that mouse-look actually responds. So I can't assume mouse works either.\n\n**Three taps will pinpoint the exact layer — 10 seconds, then I know the fix.** Hit Play, then:\n\n| Press | Tell me |\n|---|---|\n| **Spacebar** | does he **jump**? |\n| **` / ~ key** (above Tab, left of the 1) | does a **console text-bar** slide onto the screen? |\n| **move the mouse** | does the **camera turn**? |\n\nWhat each answer means:\n- **Spacebar jumps** → your keyboard *is* reaching Unreal; it's a WASD-specific mapping thing and I fix it in the project in ~2 min.\n- **Spacebar does nothing AND ~ does nothing** → your keys aren't reaching Unreal at all → it's your keyboard/its software (Razer/Corsair/Windows), *not* the game. \n- **Mouse turns but no keys work** → confirms keyboard-only block (same conclusion, keyboard software).\n\nAnd the **killer test if you have any wired/USB keyboard handy**: plug it in, try WASD in the game. If the wired one works, it's definitively your wireless keyboard's software swallowing keys — and I'll walk you straight to the toggle that fixes it.\n\nGive me those results and I'll land this.","background_tasks":[],"session_crons":[]}
