[2026-07-01T21:54:25Z] PRE-TOOL-USE: INPUT: {"session_id":"8900910c-7bda-454a-95ef-12a1e503c884","transcript_path":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-jackw-Desktop-PoolHop\\8900910c-7bda-454a-95ef-12a1e503c884.jsonl","cwd":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\Desktop\\PoolHop","prompt_id":"948baa45-6f20-426f-9166-3cc47a65e9cf","permission_mode":"bypassPermissions","effort":{"level":"max"},"hook_event_name":"PreToolUse","tool_name":"Write","tool_input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-jackw-Desktop-PoolHop\\memory\\input-dead-was-hollow-imc-assets.md","content":"---\nname: input-dead-was-hollow-imc-assets\ndescription: PoolHop's \"game runs but ignores all input\" was IMC assets saved to disk with EMPTY Mappings — editor-session verification tested in-memory state, not disk; verify via cold standalone launch + console GetAll.\nmetadata:\n  type: project\n---\n\nPoolHop (2026-07-01, commit `f5c714e`): the days-long \"hit Play, nothing responds\" bug was NOT focus/perf/wiring — the on-disk `IMC_Default`/`IMC_MouseLook` uassets had **empty `Mappings` arrays**. MCP-authored mappings existed only in that editor session's memory; every cold-from-disk launch had zero key bindings. Fixed by restoring template input assets (`UE_5.8\\Templates\\TemplateResources\\High\\Input\\Content\\` → same `/Game/Input/` paths) + engine-level `DefaultMappingContexts` in `Config/DefaultInput.ini`. Crouch/Sprint mappings still need re-adding via MCP (template IMC lacks them); `BP_PlayerController`'s BeginPlay bytecode is stale on disk (never runs cold — harmless now, resave later).\n\n**Why:** editor-session \"verified\" (PIE right after authoring) exercises dirty in-memory objects, and `save_assets` can silently write hollow shells. String-grepping a uasset only proves import-table references, not array contents.\n\n**How to apply:** trust only cold-process verification — standalone `-game` launch, then in-game console `GetAll InputMappingContext Mappings` (dumps runtime asset state to the log). See [[sendinput-probe-selftest-capability]] and the repo skill `.claude/skills/unreal-input-probe/`. Related: [[freeze-was-static-anim-not-perf]].\n"},"tool_use_id":"toolu_0114UNBjxwybBM87DYkNaWAo"}
