[2026-07-01T21:54:32Z] PRE-TOOL-USE: INPUT: {"session_id":"8900910c-7bda-454a-95ef-12a1e503c884","transcript_path":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-jackw-Desktop-PoolHop\\8900910c-7bda-454a-95ef-12a1e503c884.jsonl","cwd":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\Desktop\\PoolHop","prompt_id":"948baa45-6f20-426f-9166-3cc47a65e9cf","permission_mode":"bypassPermissions","effort":{"level":"max"},"hook_event_name":"PreToolUse","tool_name":"Write","tool_input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-jackw-Desktop-PoolHop\\memory\\sendinput-probe-selftest-capability.md","content":"---\nname: sendinput-probe-selftest-capability\ndescription: PowerShell SendInput CAN drive Unreal Enhanced Input end-to-end (synthetic Slate keys can't) — full no-MCP drive/observe toolkit exists as the unreal-input-probe skill in the PoolHop repo.\nmetadata:\n  type: project\n---\n\nThe old \"MCP cannot self-test a hardware keypress\" wall in PoolHop is broken: **OS-level `SendInput` from PowerShell produces real WM_KEYDOWN/raw-input that Enhanced Input consumes like a physical keyboard** (proven: WASD run, mouse-look, Space jump, all injected). Focus the game window with a real click (`SetCursorPos`+`mouse_event`) — bypasses `SetForegroundWindow` restrictions; find the window by PID via EnumWindows; observe with GDI `CopyFromScreen` (no masking, unlike computer-use); drive the tilde console the same way (`showdebug enhancedinput`, `GetAll <Class> <Prop>` → log file).\n\n**Why:** enables full runtime gameplay verification in sessions where unreal-mcp never connected (it only connects at Claude-session start), and is the only honest test of hardware-path input.\n\n**How to apply:** scripts + doctrine live in `PoolHop/.claude/skills/unreal-input-probe/` (`probe-input.ps1`, `send-console.ps1`). Warn the user before running (moves their real mouse/keyboard ~10 s). Related: [[input-dead-was-hollow-imc-assets]].\n"},"tool_use_id":"toolu_018X2RVnEvTQPQs3Po8YZXpD"}
