[2026-07-01T21:58:45Z] STOP-HOOK: INPUT: {"session_id":"8900910c-7bda-454a-95ef-12a1e503c884","transcript_path":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-jackw-Desktop-PoolHop\\8900910c-7bda-454a-95ef-12a1e503c884.jsonl","cwd":"C:\\Users\\jackw\\Desktop\\PoolHop","prompt_id":"948baa45-6f20-426f-9166-3cc47a65e9cf","permission_mode":"bypassPermissions","effort":{"level":"max"},"hook_event_name":"Stop","stop_hook_active":false,"last_assistant_message":"# Done — the input bug is dead, and you confirmed it yourself: you can move. 🏊\n\n**What was actually wrong, in one sentence:** the input mapping assets (`IMC_Default`, `IMC_MouseLook`) were saved to disk with **empty mappings arrays** — the WASD/look/jump bindings authored via MCP last week only ever existed in that editor session's memory, so every time *you* hit Play (a cold load from disk), the game had literally zero key bindings while the world ran fine at 120fps. It was never focus, never perf, never the graph wiring — everyone verified the Blueprint graphs and nobody verified the asset *content on disk*.\n\n**How I proved it without the MCP** (it can't connect this session — editor was closed at session start): launched the game standalone and drove it with **OS-level `SendInput`** — real hardware-path input that Enhanced Input accepts, unlike the synthetic keys that failed before. The tilde console opened (so raw keyboard reached the game), and `GetAll InputMappingContext Mappings` printed both IMCs loaded-but-empty. Smoking gun on screen: *\"No enhanced player input action mappings have been applied to this input.\"*\n\n**The fix** (commits `f5c714e`, `5a6ad3a`, pushed):\n1. Restored pristine `IMC_Default`/`IMC_MouseLook`/`IA_Move/Look/MouseLook/Jump` from the engine's template stash (same package paths — the Mannequins trick again).\n2. Added engine-level `DefaultMappingContexts` in [DefaultInput.ini](Config/DefaultInput.ini) so every player gets the contexts applied by C++ — input no longer depends on any Blueprint BeginPlay.\n3. Verified end-to-end on a cold launch: WASD run with animation, mouse-look, Space jump — all captured on screen.\n\n**Your popup:** that was the editor offering to restore stale auto-saves from the broken era — restoring could have clobbered the fixed input assets, so I declined it by removing the restore manifest (auto-save files preserved for forensics). The editor is now **up and clean with the MCP server listening on port 8000**, so hit Play whenever you like — and the next Claude session will connect to the MCP properly.\n\n**Still open (small):** Crouch and Sprint keys aren't mapped yet (the template IMC doesn't have them — needs a quick MCP session to re-add `C` and `LeftShift`, then *verify on disk*), and `BP_PlayerController` should be recompiled/resaved since its saved bytecode is stale. Both are noted in [CLAUDE.md](CLAUDE.md) as the next session's first tasks.\n\nEverything you watched me do — the console (`showdebug enhancedinput`, `GetAll`), the SendInput probe, the GDI screenshots — is written up in [LESSONS.md](Docs/LESSONS.md) and captured as a reusable skill with scripts at [.claude/skills/unreal-input-probe/](.claude/skills/unreal-input-probe/SKILL.md). I can see you've sent a follow-up about auditing the docs and prepping a handoff for a cheaper model — that message hasn't formally reached me yet, so I'll dig into it the moment it lands.","background_tasks":[],"session_crons":[]}
